<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 8:12PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern Anson,
southwestern Montgomery, northwestern Richmond and Stanly Counties
through 900 PM EDT...
At 812 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Albemarle to near Midland. Movement was
southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Wadesboro, Badin Lake, Ansonville, Sturdivants, Polkton,
Locust, Norwood, Badin and Oakboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
these storms pass.</instruction>
